## Phase 4: User Story 7 - Undo/Redo with Clear History (Priority: P1)

**Goal**: Content editors can undo and redo changes with confidence that all edits are tracked (block additions, deletions, reordering, content modifications)

**Independent Test**: Make various edits (add, delete, reorder, modify blocks), click undo repeatedly to verify each action reverses, then click redo to verify actions replay correctly. Verify history clears on new edit after undo.

### Tests for User Story 7

> **NOTE: Write these tests FIRST, ensure they FAIL before implementation**

- [ ] T022 [P] [US7] Create unit test for blockHistory utility in tests/unit/blockHistory.test.ts (test push, undo, redo, clear, maxSize)
- [ ] T023 [P] [US7] Create integration test for undo/redo in VisualBlockEditor in tests/integration/undoRedo.test.tsx (test undo deletion, redo, clear future on new action)

### Implementation for User Story 7

- [ ] T024 [US7] Implement History<T> class with push/undo/redo/clear methods in lib/utils/blockHistory.ts
- [ ] T025 [US7] Implement useBlockHistory hook with undo/redo state management in lib/hooks/useBlockHistory.ts
- [ ] T026 [US7] Integrate history tracking into BlockEditorContext in contexts/BlockEditorContext.tsx
- [ ] T027 [US7] Add undo button to VisualBlockEditor toolbar in components/blocks/VisualBlockEditor.tsx
- [ ] T028 [US7] Add redo button to VisualBlockEditor toolbar in components/blocks/VisualBlockEditor.tsx
- [ ] T029 [US7] Update all block mutation actions (add, delete, modify, reorder) to create history entries before changes
- [ ] T030 [US7] Add keyboard shortcuts (Cmd+Z for undo, Cmd+Shift+Z for redo) to editor using mousetrap

**Checkpoint**: At this point, User Story 7 should be fully functional - undo/redo works for all block operations

